<title>J.S. Mzilikazi Khumalo, South African Composer & Choral Director</title>
<meta name="description" content="James Stephen Mzilikazi Khumalo was born on June 20, 1932 on a Salvation Army farm called KwaNgwelu or Mountain View.  Khumalo taught high school while pursuing his M.A. and Ph.D. degrees.  Composing and choral competitions have played a major role in his life, but he is also an Emeritus Professor of African Languages at the University of the Witwatersrand.  Prof. Khumalo's other positions include Vice-Chairman of the Board of Directors of SAMRO, the Southern African Musical Rights Organisation. ">
<meta name="keywords" content="African composer, African choral arranger, African choral competion director, South African composer, South African choral arranger, &quot;Ushaka&quot;">
